The paper focuses on convolutional networks and their performance in vision tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new convolution unit and analyzes its efficiency, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The proposed unit also has the potential to improve the accuracy of existing convolutional networks, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed unit in natural language processing tasks, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
